To analyze the cluster structure and construct the radial density profile (RDP), the first step is to accurately determine the cluster’s center. The primary objective is to locate the region with the highest stellar density. To achieve this, we generated a two-dimensional histogram of star counts in right ascension (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
