A precise interstellar dust extinction law is critically important for interpreting observations. Extinction coefficients for each passband depend on the source’s spectral energy distribution, interstellar matter, and the extinction itself. Both the color excess ratio (CER), \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
